## 📝 설계 패턴

### 패턴 1: 설정 저장소

```rust
struct Config {
    data: HashMap<String, String>,
}

impl Config {
    fn new() -> Self {
        Config {
            data: HashMap::new(),
        }
    }

    fn set(&mut self, key: String, value: String) {
        self.data.insert(key, value);
    }

    fn get(&self, key: &str) -> Option<String> {
        self.data.get(key).cloned()
    }

    fn get_or_default(&self, key: &str, default: &str) -> String {
        self.data
            .get(key)
            .cloned()
            .unwrap_or_else(|| default.to_string())
    }
}

// 사용
let mut config = Config::new();
config.set("host".to_string(), "localhost".to_string());
println!("{}", config.get_or_default("host", "0.0.0.0"));
```

### 패턴 2: 단어 빈도 계산

```rust
fn count_words(text: &str) -> HashMap<&str, i32> {
    let mut counts = HashMap::new();

    for word in text.split_whitespace() {
        counts
            .entry(word)
            .and_modify(|count| *count += 1)
            .or_insert(1);
    }

    counts
}

// 사용
let text = "hello world hello rust";
let counts = count_words(text);

for (word, count) in counts {
    println!("{}: {}", word, count);
}
```

### 패턴 3: 사용자 프로필 저장

```rust
struct User {
    name: String,
    email: String,
    age: u32,
}

struct UserStore {
    users: HashMap<String, User>,
}

impl UserStore {
    fn new() -> Self {
        UserStore {
            users: HashMap::new(),
        }
    }

    fn add(&mut self, id: String, user: User) {
        self.users.insert(id, user);
    }

    fn find(&self, id: &str) -> Option<&User> {
        self.users.get(id)
    }

    fn find_by_email(&self, email: &str) -> Option<&User> {
        self.users
            .values()
            .find(|user| user.email == email)
    }
}
```

### 패턴 4: 권한 관리 시스템

```rust
struct PermissionSystem {
    permissions: HashMap<String, u32>,
}

impl PermissionSystem {
    fn new() -> Self {
        PermissionSystem {
            permissions: HashMap::new(),
        }
    }

    fn grant(&mut self, user: String, level: u32) {
        self.permissions.insert(user, level);
    }

    fn revoke(&mut self, user: &str) {
        self.permissions.remove(user);
    }

    fn has_permission(&self, user: &str, required: u32) -> bool {
        self.permissions
            .get(user)
            .map(|&level| level >= required)
            .unwrap_or(false)
    }

    fn list_all(&self) {
        for (user, level) in &self.permissions {
            println!("{}: Level {}", user, level);
        }
    }
}
```

